The paper discusses the design and implementation of a wireless channel sounding system, which involves measuring wireless propagation characteristics in specific environments. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and augmented reality (cs.AR). However, given the focus on wireless propagation measurements, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.AR.
